Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Zusätze"

- Photos of the 'Rape of the Daughters of Leucippus'
- Postcards from Tournai and Rotterdam
- Envelope with correspondence with Franz Haffner dated 1969 with a reproduction of a portrait
- Photo of the Self portrait by Rubens
- Notes about the Self portrait
- Business card of Otto Puschner
- Postcard with a reproduction of 'The Tribute Money'
- Envelope with a photo of Rubens portrait, notes and correspondence with Peter Schumacher dated 1974
- Envelope with photos of Rubens portrait and correspondence with Bruno Lohse dated 1971
- Letter about "Petrus Paulus Rubens Antiquarius" dated 1975
- Bibliographic references
- Article: 'Rubens im Keller. Gemälde wurde durch Zufall gefunden' in "Erlanger Tagblatt" dated 28.06.1975
- Article: 'Forschungszentrum über Rubens' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 02.07.1975
- Correspondence with Günter Truschinski (dated 1974), with Gisela Vogel (dated 1969), with Hansjörg Pohlmann (dated 1975)
- Envelope with a photocopy of an unintelligible painting
- Postcard with a photo of the Sunnersbergs church
- Notes about works in the Oslo Museum
- Article: 'Rubens-Gemälde beschädigt' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 18.06.1974
- Article: 'Rubens' Altarbild' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 03.01.1975
- Article: 'Kostbarkeiten aus Frankfurter Museen' dated 20.07.1974
- Reproduction (from "The Times" 30.10.1973) of a painting with a nimph, a satyr and leopards, descovered by Oscar Klein
- Invitation to the Collection Bock
- Photo of 'Nymphs surprised by Satyrs'
- Correspondence with K. F. Ertel dated 1970
- Photocopy of notes about works in the Vienna Academy (dated 1967)
- Brochure of "Rubens: The Antwerp Altarpieces. The Raising of the Cross and the Descent from the Cross" by J. R. Martin
- Correspondence with Gerard Stern dated 1968/1970
- Article: 'Rubens in seinen Briefen. Zu einem Band von Marint Warnke' in "Die Welt" dated 08.12.1966
- Article: 'Fallstricke für Experten. Schwierigkeiten und Hilfen beim Schätzen von Bildern' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 08.12.1966
- Article: 'Rubens und sein Jahrhundert. Brüssel zeigt das Goldene Zeitalter der flämischen Malerei' in "Darmstädter Echo" dated 27.11.1965
- Article: 'Der Revolutionär Rubens. Die Ausstellung "Rubens und seine Zeit" in Brüssel"' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated  22.11.1965
- Article: 'Neuerwerbung des Städelschen Kunstinstituts: ein Rubens' dated 11.07.1964
- Article: 'Ein einziges Gemälde von Peter Paul Rubens' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 08.02.1962
- Photo of 'Bacchus and Diana'
- Booklet: "Die Rubensstecher" (Düsseldorf Art Museum), April 1965
- Figure 136 "Portrait of Susanna Fourment" in "Rubens Drawings" by L. Burchard and R. - A. d'Hulst
- Photo of the essay 'Eine neuerworbene Skizze aud sem Rubens-Kreise' by Bode, in "Amtliche Berichte aus den königl. Kunstsammlungen"
- Photo of the article 'Pedro Pablo Rubens' in "Kunst-Blatt" dated 21.10.1822
- Post card with a photo of 'Venus and Adonis'
- Correspondence with Hans Latteier dated 1970
- Photo of the 'Holy Family with Saint Elisabeth' (description on the back)
- Article: 'Kostharkeiten aus Frankfurt Museen (198)' dated 16.05.1970
- First subfolder: (Annotation: "Reinhard Liess Wahrheit und Wirklichkeit in Werke des P.P.Rubens (Braunschweig 1970)") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Professor Dr. phil Hans Gerhard Evers 6101 Traisa üb. Darmstadt Waldstr. 43":
    - Draft text "Liess"
    - Correspondence with Gosebruch dated 1970
    - Draft text "Zu "Wahrheit und Wirklichkeit in der Kunst des Peter Paul Rubens" von Reinhard Liess"
- Photos of buildings in Ghent
- Small orange envelope (Annotation: "Zu "Rubens" ") addressed to "Herrn Professor Dr. Evers Technische Hochschule Darmstadt":
    - Correspondence with Paul E. Blendinger dated 1970
    - Photo of a portrait of an Evangelist or an Apostol
- Correspondence with Franz Haffner dated 1969
- Reproduction (from "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 04.07.1969) of the 'Equestrian Portrait of the Duke of Lerma'
- Correspondence with Karl Hundertmark (dated 1969), with G. Adriani (dated 1967), with M. Röthel (dated 1971), with Karl Hundermark (dated 1969)
- Brochures of the "Monographies de l'art belge"
- Post card with a reproduction of a 'Head Study'
- Reproduction (from "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 28.06.1971) of 'Four Studies of the Head of a Negro'
- Essay: 'Some new Van Dyck Materials and Problems' by Erik Larsen, in "Raggi" vol. 7, n.1, 1967
- Photo of 'Prometheus Bound'
- Article: 'Ein Rubens fuer den Prado' in "ES Spanien Jede Woche" dated 24.02.1969
- Reproduction of the 'Landscape with Tobias and the Angel' (from "Mannheimer Hefte" 1962)
- Notes about 'Diana and Callisto'
- Second subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Christus a.d. Stroh (Antwerpen) mit Flügelbildern –
 Maria mit stehendem Jesus-Exemplar in Augsburg (1968)" addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. Hans Gerhard Evers 06101 Traisa Waldstr. 43" and dated 23.05.1968:
    - Draft text "Zu der Komposition von Rubens: "Maria mit stehendem Kind" " and description of the work
    - Extracts from different publications
    - Correspondence with van Beselaere, Herta and Franz Huber, Baudouin dated 1968
    - Notes about 'Mary with Child'
    - Photo of 'Mary with Child'
    - Draft text "Zu der Komposition "Maria mit Kind" und einer Version"
- Envelope addessed to "Herrn Professor Dr. H. G. Evers 6101 Traisa über Darmstadt Waldstraβe 43":
    - Correspondence with L. A. Latteier dated 1970
    - Photos of the 'Portrait of Helene Fourment' and a sketch of 'Achille and Briseis'
    - Extracts from different publications
- Photos of letters
